Katja and Claudia, who have recovered from eating disorders, opened the first restaurant in Germany for anorexics and bulimics.
The establishment aims to provide a safe space for those transitioning to a normal life.
Meanwhile, a study in Italy revealed the harmful impact of food commercials on children, potentially leading to eating disorders.
Additionally, research on leptin as a treatment for anorexia raised questions about addressing the root cause of the disorder.
The struggle with eating disorders extends to family dynamics and societal pressures, highlighting the need for understanding and support in recovery.
